Some Importaant Symbols

	# 	Root User
	$ 	Normal User
	~ 	Home
	/ 	Root
	. 	Current Dir
	../	One Step Backward
	../..   Two Step Backward

Ubuntu CLI commands	
	
* Becoming the root user

	$ su
	and then type password
	if error occurs then do following
	
	$ sudo -i passwd
	
	input the old password
	input the new password
	retype the password
	you have got the root privileges

* Clearing the Screen

	$ clear
	
* Changing dirctory

	$ cd dirname
	
	direcctory must be in the current dir
	
	$ cd -
	prev dir
	
	
   * Going to home
   
  	when you are moving to any dir to home
  	
  	$ cd ~
  	
  	when you are in the root
  	
  	$ cd /home
  	
   * Going to root
   
  	$ cd /
  	
   * Going one step back of dir
   
  	$ cd ..
  	
   * Going two step backward from current
   
  	$ cd ../../

* Listing the contents of dir
   
   * Listing unhidden files

	$ ls

	$ la

	$ l

   * Listing all files

  	$ ls -a
  	
   * Accessing files with full information
   	$ ls -l
   
   * Accessing in different forms
	$ ls -R
	recursive
	
	$ ls -r
	recursive while sorting
	
	$ ls -t
	modification wise
	
* Creating the directory

	$ mkdir dirname

* Removing the Files

   * Empty directory

  	$ rmdir dirname

   * Nonemty directory or any file

  	$ rm -r file/dirname
  	
  	or
  	
  	$ rm filename
  	
   * Delete all file with certain extension	

   	$ rm *.extension
  	
* Creating a file 
 	
 	$ touch filename


 	
